# Rust build artifacts
/target/
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk

# Cargo lockfile is committed for reproducible builds (this is a workspace
# with binary targets in later sessions).

# Editor / IDE state
/.idea/
/.vscode/
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo

# Tree-sitter / grammar dev artifacts that regenerate
/grammar/node_modules/
/grammar/build/
/grammar/.venv/
/grammar/__pycache__/
/grammar/*.so

# Test snapshots that should not be committed
**/*.snap.new
**/*.pending-snap

# CLAN / analysis-program side-effect output files. These programs write a
# fixed-name report or spreadsheet into whatever directory they run in (CLAN's
# CHECK drops `00errors.cex`; EVAL and friends drop `*.evald.xls`; FREQ
# `+d2`/`+d3`/`+d20` drop `stat.frq*.xls`, and `+dCN` (percent-of-speakers)
# drops `words.frq*.xls`). They are regenerated artifacts,
# never source, and must never be committed (four were accidentally swept into
# corpus/reference/ by the foundational import). The committed spreadsheet
# parity goldens are `.clan.txt`, so this pattern never matches them.
**/00errors.cex
**/*.evald.xls
**/stat.frq*.xls
**/words.frq*.xls

# Logs and temporary scratch
*.log
/scratch/
/.tooling/

# mdBook build output
/book/build/
